AB  - This paper analyzes the welfare and economic implications of an interest-bearing retail central bank digital currency (CBDC) as a second monetary policy instrument within a New Keynesian small open-economy model. Simulations show that a countercyclical CBDC interest rate or quantity rule enhances social welfare and economic stability. When used only domestically, an interest-bearing CBDC can overcome the macroeconomic trilemma: the interest rate on bonds effectively stabilizes exchange rate movements via uncovered interest parity, while the domestic CBDC monetary policy targets inflation.
ER  - 
